        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 22 at 8:25AM MDT until June 22 at 8:45AM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 825 AM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 14 miles north of
Morristown, or 24 miles northeast of Lemmon, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
southwestern Sioux and southwestern Grant Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
